FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS


Home
▸
FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS


WHAT ARE GKFF’S GRANT APPLICATION REQUIREMENTS?


GKFF does not accept unsolicited proposals. Instead, GKFF works directly with service providers in areas of mutual interest to develop projects in the community. Application requirements are program-specific and vary depending on the project.




TO WHAT KINDS OF PROGRAMS DOES GKFF GRANT?

GKFF invests in opportunities relevant to its areas of focus: early childhood education, social services support, civic enhancement projects and community health initiatives.




DOES GKFF HAVE A GEOGRAPHIC FOCUS IN ITS GRANT MAKING?


GKFF prefers to fund organizations and efforts related to direct service delivery to the greater Tulsa area and, occasionally elsewhere, in Oklahoma. GKFF also supports national replication of Educare and select national efforts aimed at promotion of early childhood education.





DOES GKFF PROVIDE GRANTS TO INDIVIDUALS?

No.




WHAT IS THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN GKFF AND TCF (TULSA COMMUNITY FOUNDATION)?

GKFF is a Type I 509(a)3 supporting organization of the Tulsa Community Foundation. The purpose of GKFF is to support the community, state and other charities focused principally on reducing the cycle of poverty, mainly in the greater Tulsa area.




 










