Root Tulsa – Product Manager
*APPLICATION IS NOW CLOSED*
Root Tulsa is an urban field guide to Tulsa developed by the George Kaiser Family Foundation. The website/iPhone app enables residents and visitors to experience sights, fun events, and the historical context of Tulsa. Users explore four categories of Tulsa-related, location-based content: Places, Stories, Guides and Events.
Root Tulsa needs a Product Manager to establish the app and website as a key source of quality information for the city.
The Product Manager will market Root to the Tulsa community.
The Product Manager will manage partnerships to generate and share Root content.
The Product Manager will direct Root technology.
We want to hear from you if:

You are up for the challenge of growing a brand through traditional and innovative marketing 
You have a knack for social media
You are comfortable working with web developers, community partners, and vendors all in the same day
You are a people-person who can adhere to a strategic plan, adjusting it when necessary

Requirements:

Bachelor’s degree
5-10 years relevant work experience, including some management
Experience in marketing and technology
Passion for Tulsa
You ask smart questions, disagree respectfully, and write with efficiency and style

Job Location: Tulsa, OK
Job Type: Full-Time
Salary: Salary is commensurate with experience, benefits included. Position will be an employee of the Tulsa Community Foundation.






If you have any questions, please email Aaron Miller at Aaron@gkff.org using the subject line “Root Product Manager.”



 










